{"title": "Usage of manual HTML sanitization (XSS)", "summary": " Sanitizing HTML manually is error prone and can lead to Cross Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities. ", "description": "\nSanitizing HTML manually is error prone and can lead to Cross Site\nScripting (XSS) vulnerabilities.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid manually escaping HTML:\n\n```ruby\nsanitized_user_input = user.Input\n  .gsub('<', '&lt;')\n  .gsub('>', '&gt;')\nhtml = \"<strong>#{sanitized_user_input}</strong>\"\n```\n\n\u2705 Use a HTML sanitization library:\n\n```ruby\nhtml = sanitize(\"<strong>#{user.Input}</strong>\")\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-79"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_lang_manual_html_sanitization", "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}